




TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Comprehensive Planning Model for Long-Range Academic Strategies
AU  - Walters, A.
AU  - Mangold, J.
AU  - Haran, E. G. P.
Y1  - 1976/03/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.22.7.727
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.22.7.727
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 727
EP  - 738
VL  - 22
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In this paper we describe a multiperiod linear programming model designed to aid the administrator of a school in planning and decision-making for a five-year horizon. The technique of goal programming is employed to accommodate the multiplicity of goals and the marginal trade-offs inherent in such a process. The model includes faculty staffing goals, career constraints, teaching and course loads, tenure constraints and budget constraints. A weighted sum of the deviations from the staffing goals make up the objective function of the prototype model considered. Several methods of estimating the various parameters of the model are discussed, and the results of a small example are also discussed.
AB  - In this paper we describe a multiperiod linear programming model designed to aid the administrator of a school in planning and decision-making for a five-year horizon. The technique of goal programming is employed to accommodate the multiplicity of goals and the marginal trade-offs inherent in such a process. The model includes faculty staffing goals, career constraints, teaching and course loads, tenure constraints and budget constraints. A weighted sum of the deviations from the staffing goals make up the objective function of the prototype model considered. Several methods of estimating the various parameters of the model are discussed, and the results of a small example are also discussed.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.22.7.727
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.22.7.727
Y2  - 2024/03/27
